Class NumberVectorLabelParser<V extends NumberVector<V,?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.datasource.parser.AbstractParser

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of NumberVector used
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BundleStreamSource, Parser, StreamingParser, InspectionUtilFrequentlyScanned, Parameterizable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoubleVectorLabelParser, FloatVectorLabelParser, SparseFloatVectorLabelParser, TermFrequencyParser

    public class NumberVectorLabelParser<V extends NumberVector<V,?>>
extends AbstractStreamingParser

    Provides a parser for parsing one point per line, attributes separated by whitespace.

    Several labels may be given per point. A label must not be parseable as double. Lines starting with "#" will be ignored.

    An index can be specified to identify an entry to be treated as class label. This index counts all entries (numeric and labels as well) starting with 0.
